    <h2>Fisher & Paykel — NZ heritage, Huntington Beach parts chain</h2>
    <p>Fisher & Paykel was founded in 1934 in Auckland, New Zealand as an appliance manufacturer and has maintained its engineering + design headquarters in Auckland across multiple ownership eras. Haier Group acquired F&P in 2012, and despite the Chinese corporate ownership, F&P continues to operate as an independent premium brand within the Haier portfolio with NZ engineering leadership preserved. This matters for LA customers in specific ways: F&P's product engineering reflects NZ design values — understated design language, flush-mount integrated-kitchen aesthetic, premium build quality — rather than being absorbed into mainstream Haier product lines.</p>
    <p>The operational signature for LA service is F&P USA's Huntington Beach California headquarters and parts warehouse. F&P established Huntington Beach as the North American base, which gives LA service a parts-chain advantage comparable to Hestan (Anaheim) and BSH brands (Irvine): common F&P wall oven parts run 1-3 days through Huntington Beach, versus 3-7+ days for out-of-state-sourced luxury brands. Specialty F&P components (current-generation Series 9 control boards, CombiSteam hardware, Pyrolytic thermal sensors) run 3-5 days.</p>
  </div></section>

