  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Series 9 flush-mount discipline — LA modernist kitchens</h2>
    <p>Series 9 is F&P's pro-style flagship and its primary differentiator is the flush-mount installation tolerance that lets the unit sit precisely flush with surrounding cabinetry. For LA customers renovating Case Study homes, Eichler kitchens, or contemporary architectural projects, Series 9 fills a specific aesthetic niche — pro-grade capability without the pro-style commercial-kitchen visual.</p>
    <p>Our Series 9 service discipline preserves flush-mount integrity across every service call — partial-pull method for service access rather than default full-pull, cabinet-preservation pads to prevent panel scratches, shim adjustment at reinstall, gap-line verification at all four edges top/bottom/left/right. This discipline is the same approach we apply to Miele H 7000 work because the aesthetic expectations are comparable — both brands appeal to integrated-kitchen buyers who expect precision alignment through the appliance's service life.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Pyrolytic self-clean 900°F service</h2>
    <p>F&P's Pyrolytic self-clean is a signature feature — cavity runs to approximately 900°F to carbonize food residue into ash. The high-temperature cycle stresses several components and requires specific service attention:</p>
    <p><b>Door-lock motor</b> — cycle won't start without confirmed door-lock engagement (safety-critical). Motor fails from cumulative cycle wear. Replacement $280-$460.</p>
    <p><b>Thermal sensor</b> — control board monitors cavity temperature throughout the cycle; if sensor drift exceeds spec, board aborts cycle as safety measure. Replacement $260-$420.</p>
    <p><b>Control-board self-clean firmware</b> — cycle logic sometimes hits a firmware edge case and aborts; factory reset + firmware update often resolves without full board replacement.</p>
    <p><b>Cavity envelope integrity</b> — Pyrolytic cycle requires cavity seal to maintain the 900°F envelope; door-gasket degradation over years can let the cycle run hot elsewhere and trigger safety aborts. Gasket replacement $220-$380 when degradation is the root cause.</p>
  </div></section>

